<br>
His presence was well known within this city - he was no enemy to those within, however his business was his own, and simple enchantments such as these kept his business from the normal rumor lines.<br>
<br>
He walked quickly through the alleyways towards Harvester Hall, the guards equipped to see him smirked slyly, and nodded his passage on.  He passed the main hall, and instead went to the lounge where those who sought to join the hall stayed.<br>
<br>
The shadows fell from him with a mere thought, revealing the bard fully.  He was not overly tall, his stature muscular and well honed.  His face showed a mere two decades, though his haunted blue eyes seemed as if from a much older man.  His platinum hair was cut short to accomidate a helm, and a simple gotee and mustache surrounded his lips.  White armor clad his body, a very old mandolin graced his back, and two swords sat in their sheathes on his belt.<br>
<br>
He spoke in precise Teir'Dal, his voice clear and somewhat jovial.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Mi'lady Kerridwynn.  I have come to speak further of joining your family. <p>~Falcolas Swiftsong~ Virtuoso<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gray;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=318126">Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->[/center]</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerridwynn>Kerridwynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ilharess of the Scythe</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(9/8/03 10:29 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/Kerridwynn2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Bard</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn looked up at the bard, laying the book she had been reading across her lap.  She smiled at him, gesturing elegantly for him to sit if he wished. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;Falcolas, welcome.  Come sit, and we will talk.  I must say I had hoped to hear from you.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>She leaned back in her chair, looking at a servant standing ready near a doorway.  With a nod of her head, she sent the young woman scurrying for drinks.  Kerridwynn turned back to the man before her, and smiled again, her eyes lighting softly with indigo flames.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;You've already proven yourself to me, looking after my daughter as you have, and lending your hand whenever I had need as well.  You are a marvelous talespinner, and an excellent friend.  I am glad to see you here, seeking entry to Harvester Hall.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn looked up as the servant returned and crossed the room to stand quietly near them.  With a smile, the priestess took the drinks from the tray the girl held, and handed the goblet of champayne to Falcolas, raising her own glass of wine to her lips in a silent toast.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;I fear you will not have an easy time of it, but I remain hopeful that my family may put aside whatever experiences they may have had in the past, and welcome you as they would any other who comes seeking our paths.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn closed her eyes for a moment, then opened them again.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;You will need to meet Silenae before I can welcome you to the family.&quot; <p><center><img src="http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/Kerridwynn.jpg"><BR><i>~*Templar of Luclin, the Maiden of Shadows*~<br>~*Mistress of the Scythe*~</i><br><i>The hours go by like minutes,<br>And the shadows come to stay.</i><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness>Harvesters of Darkness</a><br>~~~~~~~~~~<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=208851>Garb of the Priestess</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ankhami>Ankhami</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Yath'tallar of Vengance<br>
Demaste's Second</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(9/9/03 12:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Bard</span><hr size=1> Ankhami listens to the conversation, from the door. Slowly after Kerridwynn's last words she makes her way to her room. <br>
Why did the ones before have to make it hard for the ones to come? Falcolas had proven him self, and yet his fate hung in the balance because of another bard. <br>
She hoped that the one she called sis, could see beyond the class, and look into the person Falcolas was. Ahh well, time would tell. And what ever the outcome, she would stand behind her family. But no matter the out come, Falcolas would always be welcome to hunt and converse with her. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://w1.853.telia.com/~u85323368/sigstart.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub62.ezboard.com/btempleofsaryrn">The Temple</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=falcolas>Falcolas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(9/9/03 9:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Bard</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Falcolas made note of the discomfort on Kerridwynn's face, as well as the apprehensiveness on Ankhami's.  He offers each a reassuring smile.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I am afraid I have not yet met Silenae, and I judge from your reactions that she will... have reservations about my mere presence.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Falcolas suprises both then by simply chuckling merrily.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Let us meet then, and let us discuss.  For nothing is learned by worrying.  And I simply taste awful as a main course at dinner... too stringy in my old age.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>His eyes twinkle in the light.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p>~Falcolas Swiftsong~ Virtuoso<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gray;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=318126">Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silenaeonfirionavie>Silenae on FirionaVie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ambassador of the Scythe<br>
Bonemistress</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(9/11/03 4:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://w1.853.telia.com/~u85323368/rose1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Bard</span><hr size=1> She sits upstairs in her chambers. A messenger did bring notice of the arrival of the bard. For a time, she ponders to send it back with a note. Finally, she decides, and takes up a pen.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Greetings, Bard,<br>
<br>
i have heard tales about you from Ankhami. She has told me you would seek to become one of the Harvesters. Perhaps she also told you of my views towards your kind. If not, i am sure Kerridwynn has mentioned it.<br>
<br>
Oddly enough, your visits brings up memories.. memories i had hoped that would never return. Thoughts of my childhood, and memories of the biggest mistake made. I do not intend to repeat that mistake.<br>
<br>
Once i accepted the challenge. Now i deny it. You will not find acceptance or welcome in my words or actions.<br>
<br>
Silenae do'Bauthin<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
once finished, she rereads it several times. So many things were left unsaid, so many questions may arise. Still, she hoped the Bard would catch the meaning, and act accordingly. With a sigh, she hands the note to the messenger.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Take this below, and read it to the Bard. Then hand it to the bard, so that he can, if he wishes, reread it himself.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
The messenger hurries out following her instructions. And while her words echo through the hall, spoken by another, she sits back, lost in thoughts and memories.<br>
 <p>Silenae Do'Bauthin<br><br><br>
