<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>His voice remained low, the tone amazingly cheerful.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Memories... they define who we are, shape our future and our actions.  I can not fault her for this.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>He motions for a quill, and scribes below her short note his own.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Lady Silenae,<br>
<br>
Then I shall not seek your welcome or acceptance for a time.  I would, however, like to speak with you at your leisure, on a topic dear to both of our hearts.<br>
<br>
Memories.<br>
<br>
Humbly,<br>
<br>
Falcolas Swiftsong<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>He hands the note back to the servent, and stands with a smile.  He bows to, then hugs both of the women briefly.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Time is nothing if not on my side.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>He leaves, the shadows gathering about him once more.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p>~Falcolas Swiftsong~ Virtuoso<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gray;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=318126">Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=falcolas>Falcolas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(9/17/03 12:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Bard</span><hr size=1> Falcolas sits quietly in his sparse room in the Temple, a blank piece of parchment before him.  With a sigh, he dips a quill in ink, his flowing script beginning to fill the page.<br>
<br>
Kerridwynn, Demaste, Harvesters.<br>
<br>
I have long considered my application to your hall, after learning of the pain my application has caused.  I understand fully your desire to speak this through, and come up with a solution for the greater good of the family, and I also understand that it is likely that my application would be accepted.<br>
<br>
I am, however, a prideful man, and can not accept that knowing as I do the pain my acceptance would bring, despite any greater good caused by it.  Hence, I withdraw my application.<br>
<br>
This does not change my regard for you in any way, and I hope that I will always be welcome as a guest within your halls.<br>
<br>
Until we see each other again,<br>
<br>
Falcolas Swiftsong<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>He inspects what he has written, and folds the parchment, handing it to a messanger.  It would have to do.  He just hoped they understood.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kyimera>Kyimera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(9/18/03 8:54 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Bard</span><hr size=1> Kyimera reads over the parchement that had just been delivered. Quickly scanning the contents her head slowly lowers and her eyes close in sadness. Turning to the stair she quickly assends. Her eyes start to glow softly in frustration. He has no home, she thought to her self, and now...<br>
Parchment gripped in her hand up she knocks on her mothers door.  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=%2fAnkhami%2ffullsize%2fKyiPainting1.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerridwynn>Kerridwynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ilharess of the Scythe</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(9/18/03 2:57 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/Kerridwynn2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Bard</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn looks up at the knock on her door, eyes glowing softly.  She'd heard the messenger arrive, and wondered what the news was.  Now, she bid her daughter to enter.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
